Mexican Tourism Income Up 
Tourism in Mexico brought in 4.32 billion U.S. dollars in the first
half of this year, up 11. 3 percent over the same period in 1999.
According to the Secretariat of Tourism, the income came from the
pockets of 10.5 million foreign tourists.
Tourism in Mexico, a country that ranks eighth in the world in terms of
having the most tourist attractions, will be as prosperous in 2001 as
this year, the Secretariat said.
